title.narrative: OPT 1. 7. CONTINUED ACCESS HEALTH, NUTRITION & ECE-ECD SERV

description.narrative: Promote and ensure that women and children have continued access to essential health, immunization, prenatal and postnatal, HIV, nutrition, gender-based violence (GBV) response care, and early education services,which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Early Childhood Development, Early Childhood Development (Covid), Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid), Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, children between 0 and 5 have access to Integrated Early Childhood Development (IECD) services to guarantee that they survive and thrive, including in emergency situations.

description.narrative: UNICEF's actions aim to provide continuity health, nutrition, and comprehensive care services for early childhood, as well as care for pregnant women in areas required by the country. Main activities included delivering biosafety material and equipment to health centers to prevent the spread of COVID 19 among health personnel, so there is no absenteeism from work and thus contribute to the continuity of services for children, adolescents, and women. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:21/08/2020
